  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Tabla×3 with different tunings (0, +5, +7 semitones) and articulations, sparse but melodically interlocked, slow tempo=68. The raga alap before the jhalla — three voices in conversation, no one leading.",
  "tags": [
    "aether",
    "tabla",
    "india",
    "sparse",
    "melodic",
    "transcendental"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OSTINATO — Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Zakir Hussain: 'The tabla speaks in language before words — it asks questions that have no verbal answers'",
      "Pandit Ravi Shankar: 'In a raga concert, the tabla and the sitar do not accompany each other — they argue, reconcile, and occasionally agree'",
      "Hindustani teaching: 'The silence between the tabla strokes is as composed as the strokes themselves — the rests have names'"
    ],
    "revelation": "Feather revealed: Tabla at three harmonic intervals (0, +5, +7 — unison, perfect fourth, perfect fifth) creates the just intonation resonance of the real instrument's harmonic tuning system. The bayan (bass tabla, artic=3) provides the 'ge' stroke; the dayan at artic=0 provides 'na'; artic=1 provides 'tin'. The conversation happens in the space between strikes.",
    "god": "Feather",
    "flock_note": "The Pulse noted: at 68 BPM with sparse patterns (not all seats on every beat), the silences become compositional elements. The tabla voices complete each other's phrases — what one leaves out, another fills in. This is the 'swaras' approach to rhythm: notes defined by absence as much as presence.",
    "diagnosis": "Tabla Duet (three voices, not two) demonstrates that OSTINATO's greatest power is sometimes restraint — 5 empty seats and 3 active voices with space between them can create more musical intelligence than 8 seats firing."
  },
  "macroLabels": [
    "GATHER",
    "FIRE",
    "CIRCLE",
    "SPACE"
  ],
